Devious: (...Almost out of time...must...)
Devious: My precious samples...!?
Devious: Are all gone!?
Devious: Who dares...steal my sample!?
Devious: Forget it! I won't bicker with those petty lowlifes!
Devious: Luckily, I've got that Feather Clan boy to count on. Once I'm reincarnated into his healthy body, I'll give them what they deserve!
Devious: G...Gone!?
Nikola: This pathetic behavior really suits you. Snakes are meant to squirm on the ground~
Nikola: Oh, this is quite the experimental method. The techniques for creating immortal life really do come in levels~
Devious: You...You little...
Nikola: Ah, the Dracontine Elder has never heard little old me, has he?
Hyde: Please allow me to introduce myself. My name is Hyde Oust, a volunteer who would like to join the sect.
Devious: I've heard that name before...
Devious: Now I remember. During the Kingdom of the Sun's civil war, you're that bratty tactician who talked a big game but lost like a groveling fool!
Hyde: ...I didn't consider that Queen Angelia would be suspicious. This is why I lost, you are correct.
Hyde: That is to say, I won't let that happen again.
Hyde: Hiding these experiments from the sect, you really are quite ambitious~
Hyde: If the data from these experiments is given to the higher ups, that should be enough to atone for my sins and join the sect, no?
Devious: You've been plotting against me!?
Hyde: That's a little harsh, don't you think~
Hyde: All I did was use this eye of mine that suffers from void disease to peek into the future, that's all.
Devious: Wait...
Devious: So the one who came and saved them was——
Hyde: My good sir, do you know what's most annoying about seeing the future?
Hyde: To you this is your first time seeing this. But I've seen this drama unfold hundreds of times.
Hyde: ...I'm sick of it!
Hyde: What I saw was that the human slave was needed to ruin your plan and force you to show yourself.
Hyde: That way I could slip into your laboratory and steal your research data.
Devious: ...A diversion...
Hyde: That's right. The slave was my most important chess piece~
Hyde: My eye saw that only by him destroying the pond of lights would he be drawn out, though the timing was a little off...
Hyde: This is what irks me about having the void disease.
Hyde: But everything worked out. It was not in vain that I let him live.
Devious: You scheming....
Devious: ....No no no, just temporary loose lips, that's all...
Devious: How's this, just give me that Feather Clan boy and after I'm reincarnated, I'll help you with whatever you need?
Hyde: Oh? Anything?
Devious: Yes! If what you want from the sect is money, or power, I'll give it all to you! I don't have much longer——
Hyde: Ooooo, sounds very enticing...
Devious: Hssss, well then——
Hyde: Unfortunately, when I got here, the boy was already gone.
Hyde: Even I don't know where he is. Sorry, can't help~
Devious: What!?
Hyde: Even as an Immortal, if you can't find a suitable body to be reincarnated into, then I'm afraid it's death for you~
Hyde: High Priest, you'll await death in your precious, little laboratory~
Devious: No. NO!!!!!!!
Hyde: I never thought hearing the highest of the Immortals beg for mercy would feel so wonderful~
Hyde: The least I can do is help you turn off the lights.
Hyde: Goodnight, your Highness, the eternal Immortal.
Devious: No! WAIT!!!!
Devious: Please, help me find a body. It doesn't have to be the boy from the Feather Clan. DO YOU HEAR ME!?
Devious: Don't leave me here, please...
Devious: Hey...! Can anyone hear me? Is anyone there?
Devious: Help me...help...
Devious: ...I don't want to die...
Devious: ...Is anyone here.................anyone....
